<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
115. 
<taxonomicName LSID="BCAF9E70-F8AD-5353-A0DB-2821C41575E3" authority="Balf. f., Nat. Hist. Sokotra 524. 1903. (Forbes 1903: 524)." authorityName="Balf. f., Nat. Hist. Sokotra 524. 1903. (Forbes" authorityYear="1903" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus grantii" order="Solanales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grantii">Convolvulus grantii Balf.f., Nat. Hist. Sokotra 524. 1903. (Forbes 1903: 524).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
SOCOTRA, Abd al Kuri Island, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Ogilvie-Grant exped.</emphasis>
13, 45, 46 &amp; 50 (syntypes E!, LIV).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
Herb with thickened woody taproot and a basal rosette; stems ascending to c. 30 cm, vegetative parts sericeous and with some spreading hairs. Leaves petiolate, dimorphic; rosette leaves 3.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-1.4 cm. obovate to oblanceolate-spathulate, obtuse to acute, margin entire to undulate, base attenuate onto the petiole; stem leaves 0.3-1.5(-3) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-1 cm, acute, oblanceolate, oblong or elliptic, margin deeply sinuate, base attenuate; petioles 2-5 mm long. Flowers solitary, pedunculate; peduncles c. 3 mm long; bracteoles 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.75 mm, linear; pedicels c. 3.5 mm long; outer sepals 4-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 mm, ovate, acute or shortly acuminate; corolla 10-12 mm long, white or pinkish, lobed with broadly triangular lobes, midpetaline bands pilose; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 2.5-3 mm above base; stigmas 4 mm long. Capsule glabrous; seeds glabrous. [
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, AG" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 759" refId="B234" refString="Miller, AG, Morris, M, 2004. Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago. Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh: 1 - 759" title="Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago" year="2004">Miller and Morris 2004</bibRefCitation>
: 517]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
Endemic to Abd al Kuri Island in the Socotra archipelago (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Paulay</emphasis>
1899, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Smith &amp; Lavranos</emphasis>
660; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Miller et al.</emphasis>
19032).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="139" pageNumber="140" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
Very distinct because of the rosette habit and small, sinuately-lobed stem leaves. The corolla is slightly larger than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balf. f., Proc. Roy. Soc. Edinburgh 12: 83. 1884. (Balfour" authorityYear="1884" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sarmentosus" order="Solanales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sarmentosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Convolvulus sarmentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hildebrandtii" order="Solanales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Convolvulus hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is the most herbaceous of the three species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, AG" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 759" refId="B234" refString="Miller, AG, Morris, M, 2004. Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago. Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh: 1 - 759" title="Ethnoflora of the Soqotra Archipelago" year="2004">Miller and Morris (2004</bibRefCitation>
: 517) suggest that this species is an annual but this seems to be an error.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
